# Practice with Python Files
# file methods
# for loop

'''
py4e book ex_07_01: Write a program to read through a file and print the contents of the file (line by line)
all in upper case. Executing the program will look as follows:
'''

fhand = open('mbox-short.txt')
for line in fhand:
    line = line.rstrip()
    print(line.upper())
